### Figma Import Rules (For AI Agent)

- **Convert absolute positioning** from Figma to flexbox/grid layouts. Never use `position: absolute` for page layout.
- **Map Figma token names** directly to CSS custom properties: Figma `ld-semantic-color-text` → CSS `var(--ld-semantic-color-text)`.
- Figma inline `style=""` attributes represent design intent, not code format — always convert to CSS module classes.
- **Always export and use Figma images.** If an image exists in the Figma design, extract and use it — never substitute with a gray box, placeholder `<div>`, or generic stock image. Missing export settings are a designer error to fix, not a reason to skip the image.
- **Preserve SVGs exactly** as designed unless an identical icon already exists in `@/components/icons`.
- **Circular images/flags**: Use SVG with `<clipPath>` circles, not `border-radius` on `<img>`.
- When Figma shows multiple frames/breakpoints, implement one responsive component that handles all breakpoints via CSS media queries, not separate components.

### File Naming Convention (HARD RULE)

All files MUST follow these naming patterns consistently:

| File type | Convention | Examples |
|---|---|---|
| All UI components (LD) | **PascalCase** | `Button.tsx`, `Dialog.tsx`, `ScrollArea.tsx` |
| CSS modules | **PascalCase** (match component) | `Button.module.css`, `DataTable.module.css` |
| Pages | **PascalCase** | `Index.tsx`, `Catalog.tsx`, `DetailItem.tsx` |
| Page CSS modules | **camelCase** | `detailItem.module.css`, `landingSummary.module.css` |
| React hooks | **camelCase** with `use` prefix | `useMobile.tsx`, `useSnackbar.ts`, `useLocalStorage.ts` |
| Context files | **PascalCase** | `ThemeContext.tsx`, `MartyContext.tsx`, `ThemeRegistry.ts` |
| Feature components | **PascalCase** | `MartyAvatar.tsx`, `CatalogHero.tsx`, `MartyUtils.ts` |
| Icon components | **PascalCase** | `ArrowRight.tsx`, `ChevronDown.tsx` |
| Example files | **PascalCase** + `Example` suffix | `ButtonExample.tsx`, `TextAreaExample.tsx` |
| Token CSS files | **lowercase** | `semantic.css`, `primitive.css` |

**Never mix conventions within the same folder.** If you create a new file, check sibling files and match their naming pattern.

### File Organization

- Break complex pages into smaller component files under `client/features/[feature]/`.
- Each page gets its own CSS module in `client/styles/`.
- UI primitives go in `client/components/ui/` with their own `.module.css`.
- Check `guidelines/` folder for component documentation before creating new components.

