### Design System Package Ingestion (HARD RULE)

When a designer drops a new design system package (folder of files) into the project via Code View, the agent MUST follow this exact process:

#### Step 1: Create the staging folder

Create a folder called `design-system-package/` at the project root. All dropped files go here first. This is a temporary staging area — files are never used directly from this folder.

```
design-system-package/       # Staging area for dropped DS files
├── components/              # New/updated component source files
├── icons/                   # New/updated icon files
├── tokens/                  # Updated CSS token files
├── assets/                  # Fonts, illustrations, animations
├── docs/                    # Component docs, MDX files, README
└── README.md                # Package instructions (READ THIS FIRST)
```

#### Step 2: Read the package instructions

Before touching any files, read ALL documentation in the package:

1. Read `design-system-package/README.md` (or any README/INSTRUCTIONS file)
2. Read any `CHANGELOG.md` or `MIGRATION.md` files
3. Read any `.md` or `.mdx` doc files to understand what changed
4. Identify: what components are new, what components are updated, what was removed

#### Step 3: Reorganize files to match the project structure

Move files from `design-system-package/` to their correct locations in the project, matching the existing file structure exactly:

| Package contents | Project destination |
|---|---|
| Components (`.tsx` + `.module.css`) | `client/components/ui/` |
| Example files | `client/components/examples/` |
| Icon components (`.tsx`) | `client/components/icons/` |
| Custom icons | `client/components/icons-custom/` |
| CSS token files (primitive/semantic) | `client/styles/themes/` (for base tokens) AND `public/styles/themes/` (for runtime theme switching) |
| Font files | `public/fonts/` |
| Illustrations/SVGs | `public/illustrations/` |
| Animation JSON (Lottie) | `public/animations/` |
| Component documentation (`.md`, `.mdx`) | `design-system-docs/` |
| Guidelines/rules documentation | `guidelines/` or `guidelines/components/` |

**CRITICAL**: Preserve the project's file naming conventions:
- All UI components use **PascalCase**: `Button.tsx`, `Dialog.tsx`, `ScrollArea.tsx`, `AlertDialog.tsx`
- CSS modules match their component: `Button.module.css`, `DataTable.module.css`
- Token files use **lowercase**: `semantic.css`, `primitive.css`
- Icon components use **PascalCase**: `ArrowRight.tsx`, `ChevronDown.tsx`

#### Step 4: Replace old components with new ones

For each updated component in the package:

1. **Compare the old and new versions** — read the existing file in `client/components/ui/` and the new version from the package
2. **Replace the file** — overwrite the old component with the new one
3. **Check for breaking API changes** — if props were renamed, added, or removed:
   - Search the entire codebase for usages of the old component
   - Update all import paths and prop usage to match the new API
4. **Run typecheck** (`pnpm typecheck`) after each batch of replacements to catch breaks early

For updated **icons**:
1. Replace icon files in `client/components/icons/`
2. Check if `client/components/icons/index.tsx` needs updating (new exports, removed exports)
3. Search for usages of any removed icons and replace with the new equivalent

For updated **tokens/CSS**:
1. Replace token files in `client/styles/themes/base/` (primitive.css, semantic.css)
2. Replace corresponding files in `public/styles/themes/` for all affected themes
3. Check `client/global.css` for any hardcoded values that should now use updated tokens
4. Search for old token names that may have been renamed

For updated **assets** (fonts, illustrations, animations):
1. Replace files in `public/fonts/`, `public/illustrations/`, or `public/animations/`
2. Check for any references to old filenames that may have changed

#### Step 5: Clean up

1. **Delete the staging folder**: Remove `design-system-package/` entirely after all files have been distributed
2. **Remove any leftover markdown** from component folders — docs belong in `guidelines/` or `design-system-docs/`, never in `client/components/ui/`
3. **Remove duplicates** — if the same file exists in multiple locations, keep only the canonical copy
4. **Run typecheck**: `pnpm typecheck` must pass with zero errors
5. **Verify the dev server** still runs without errors

#### Step 6: Report what changed

After completing the ingestion, provide a summary:
- Components added (new)
- Components updated (replaced)
- Components removed (deleted)
- Icons added/updated/removed
- Tokens changed
- Any breaking changes that required code updates
- Confirmation that typecheck passes

### Common Mistakes to Avoid

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG — hardcoded colors
<div style={{ backgroundColor: '#F8F8F8', color: '#2E2F32' }}>

// ❌ WRONG — max-width constraining page content
.contentContainer { max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto; }

// ❌ WRONG — centering page content instead of stretching
.contentArea { align-items: center; }

// ❌ WRONG — custom button with inline styles
<button className="bg-blue-500 px-4 py-2 rounded-full">Click</button>

// ❌ WRONG — forcing button width with inline styles or custom classes
<Button variant="primary" UNSAFE_style={{ width: '200px' }}>Save</Button>
<Button variant="primary" UNSAFE_className="w-full">Save</Button>

// ❌ WRONG — manual star rendering
<StarFill style={{ color: '#FFC220' }} />

// ✅ CORRECT — tokens in CSS modules
.container { background: var(--ld-semantic-color-background-subtle, #f8f8f8); }

// ✅ CORRECT — full-width content
.contentArea { align-items: stretch; }

// ✅ CORRECT — button hugs text (default, no width prop needed)
<Button variant="primary" size="medium">Click</Button>

// ✅ CORRECT — button fills container width (use isFullWidth prop)
<Button variant="primary" size="medium" isFullWidth>Click</Button>

// ✅ CORRECT — use LD Rating component
<Rating value={4.4} size="small" />

// ❌ WRONG — custom hardcoded table
<table><thead><tr><th>Name</th></tr></thead></table>

// ✅ CORRECT — use DataTable system (always rounded by default)
<DataTable>
  <DataTableHead><DataTableRow>...</DataTableRow></DataTableHead>
  <DataTableBody>...</DataTableBody>
</DataTable>

// ❌ WRONG — custom tab implementation
<div className="tabs"><button className="active">Tab 1</button></div>

// ✅ CORRECT — use Tab component
<Tabs value={activeTab} onValueChange={setActiveTab}>
  <TabList><Tab value="tab1">Tab 1</Tab></TabList>
  <TabPanel value="tab1">Content</TabPanel>
</Tabs>

// ❌ WRONG — raw anchor tag or custom hyperlink
<a href="/settings" className="text-blue-600 underline">Settings</a>

// ✅ CORRECT — use LD Link component
<Link href="/settings">Settings</Link>
<Link href="/help" variant="subtle">Help</Link>
```